\subsection{Hybrid LLM Integration Architecture}

A critical innovation of our platform is the hybrid approach to LLM integration that solves significant technical challenges in multi-model AI content generation.

\subsubsection{Native Google Gemini 2.5 Pro Integration}

During development, we encountered a critical issue where Google's Gemini 2.5 Pro model returned empty content when accessed through the litellm wrapper, despite successful API calls. This problem threatened the viability of using Google's latest and most capable model for content generation.

Our solution implements a hybrid architecture:

\begin{lstlisting}[language=Python, caption=Native Gemini API Integration]
def _call_native_gemini(self, model_name: str, content_prompt: str,
                       model_params: Dict[str, Any]) -> tuple[str, float]:
    """Make a direct call to Google Gemini API, bypassing litellm."""
    if model_name == "gemini/gemini-2.5-pro":
        native_model_name = "gemini-2.5-pro"

    # Configure safety settings
    safety_settings = [
        {"category": "HARM_CATEGORY_HARASSMENT", "threshold": "BLOCK_NONE"},
        {"category": "HARM_CATEGORY_HATE_SPEECH", "threshold": "BLOCK_NONE"},
        {"category": "HARM_CATEGORY_SEXUALLY_EXPLICIT", "threshold": "BLOCK_NONE"},
        {"category": "HARM_CATEGORY_DANGEROUS_CONTENT", "threshold": "BLOCK_NONE"},
    ]

    model = genai.GenerativeModel(native_model_name)
    response = model.generate_content(content_prompt,
                                    safety_settings=safety_settings)
    return response.text, latency_ms
\end{lstlisting}

This approach:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Uses native Google Generative AI library for Gemini models
    \item Maintains litellm for other providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)
    \item Provides automatic fallback mechanisms
    \item Implements comprehensive safety setting control
    \item Achieves significant performance improvements with response sizes of 3,500+ characters vs. empty responses from litellm
\end{itemize}

