\subsection{Four-Factor Optimization Algorithm}

The core innovation lies in the feed generation algorithm that explicitly optimizes for four neurochemical factors. Content is scored using the following enhanced formula:

\begin{equation}
S_{combined} = E \times w_e + L \times w_l + B \times w_b + M \times w_m + R_{serendipity} \times w_s
\end{equation}

where:
\begin{itemize}
    \item $E$ = engagement score (dopamine pathway activation, 0-1 scale)
    \item $L$ = learning score (acetylcholine pathway activation, 0-1 scale)
    \item $B$ = breakthrough potential (norepinephrine pathway activation, 0-1 scale)
    \item $M$ = mood elevation score (positive emotional impact, 0-1 scale)
    \item $w_e, w_l, w_b, w_m$ = user-configurable weights
    \item $R_{serendipity}$ = randomization factor for cognitive flexibility
    \item $w_s$ = serendipity weight for algorithmic diversity
\end{itemize}

Default weight distributions are optimized based on neurochemical research: $w_e = 0.30$, $w_l = 0.25$, $w_b = 0.25$, $w_m = 0.20$, representing a balanced approach that prioritizes social connection while maintaining strong learning and insight components.

