\textbf{Open-Source Viability:} Automated security protocols enable safe public deployment of sophisticated AI-powered social platforms.

\subsection{Broader Implications}

As social media platforms increasingly shape human cognition, behavior, and social connection, designs that explicitly consider neurochemical diversity and user well-being become critical for the future of digital social interaction. Our work provides a technical and theoretical foundation for developing social media systems that serve educational, cognitive, and well-being objectives while maintaining user engagement and satisfaction.

The integration of advanced AI technologies with evidence-based neurochemical targeting represents a new paradigm for social media platform designâ€”one that prioritizes human flourishing alongside technological innovation. As AI capabilities continue to advance, the principles and techniques demonstrated in this work provide a framework for creating digital social environments that enhance rather than diminish human cognitive and emotional well-being.

\subsection{Call for Responsible Development}

This work also highlights the critical importance of responsible AI development in social media applications. The power to systematically target neurochemical pathways carries significant ethical implications. We advocate for:

\begin{itemize}
